FBIS3-55390 "drsov005_a_94017" FBIS-SOV-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Threatens Blockade of Japan LD0601190994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1800 GMT 6 Jan 94 LD0601190994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] Everything continues to be simple in the plans of Vladimir Zhirinovskiy. At a news conference today he stated that no one can or should interfere in the affairs of the Transcaucasus or Central Asia to prevent a new Lebanon. The leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia said that he planned to occupy the position of Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, and as his first step in the ministerial post intended to invite Tokyo to sign a peace treaty. If it refuses Zhirinovskiy promises to use the Russian Navy to blockade all the Japanese islands.
